-- TECHOPS-2187: Inventory — find all untested ObjC classes
-- Run once. Saves the class list to a file for batch processing.

workflow "TECHOPS-2187 Inventory"
  inputs: repo_path (required), output_file (required)

  ask @claude-worker """
    In {repo_path}, find every Objective-C class that has NO corresponding test file.

    HOW TO SEARCH:
    1. Find all .m files under the main app source (exclude Pods/, Carthage/, vendor/).
    2. For each .m file, extract the class name from the filename (e.g. MFPFoodEntry.m → MFPFoodEntry).
    3. Check if a test file exists anywhere under mfpUnitTests/ matching *{ClassName}Test*.swift or *{ClassName}Tests*.swift.
    4. A class is "untested" if NO matching test file exists.

    OUTPUT FORMAT:
    Return ONLY a newline-separated list of untested class names, one per line.
    No headers, no explanations, no markdown — just the class names.
    Example:
    MFPFoodEntry
    MFPDiaryDay
    MFPNutritionInfo
  """ -> class_list

  write {class_list} to {output_file}

  send #techops-2187 """
    Inventory complete. Found untested classes and saved to {output_file}.
    Run the batch processor next to start generating tests.
  """
